{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ὀδύρ-ομαι</b> [ῡ], <br /> mostly used in <i>present</i> and <i>imperfect</i>, <i>Epic dialect</i> <i>imperfect</i> ὀδύρετο, ὀδύροντο (without augment), <i>Ionic dialect</i> ὀδυρέσκετο [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.119 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>future</i> ὀδῠροῦμαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 21.186, and probable reading 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 18.35 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>aorist</i> ὠδῡράμην [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 12.9, 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 1.75 (compare ἀνοδύρομαι) \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]; <i>participle</i> ὀδῡράμενος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 24.48 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: <i>aorist</i> <i>passive</i> κατ-ωδύρθην [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.117f.\">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]—In Trag. the form <b>δύρομαι</b> is required by the metre in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 273, “Pers.” 582 (Lyric poetry), 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 1218 (Lyric poetry, ὀδ- codices), 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hecuba” 740, “Med.” 159 (Lyric poetry, ὀδ- codices), and probably in [prev. author] “Andr.” 397, see below 4; in [prev. author] “Ph.” 1762, 4th-3rd c.BC: Apollodorus Comicus 8, ὀδύρομαι\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] is necessary; elsewhere either form is possible:—<b>lament, bewail,</b> a person or thing: <br /><Level3><b>__1</b></Level3> with <i>accusative</i> <i>person</i>, ὀδυρομένη φίλα τέκνα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 2.315; Ἕκτορα δάκρυ χέοντες ὀδύροντο 24.714, compare 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Coloneus” 1439, “Ant.” 693:\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] less frequently with <i>accusative</i> _of things_, ὁ δ᾽ ὀδύρετο πατρίδα γαῖαν <b>mourned for</b> it, i.e. for the want of it, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 13.219; so νόστον ὀ. 5.153, 13.379; προπηλακίσεις 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 329b; δυστυχίας 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 4.169; πάθη 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 18.41; οὐκ ὠδύραντο.. τὴν προκαταστροφήν 4th-3rd c.BC: Epicurus Philosophus “Sententiae” 40. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> with <i>genitive</i> <i>person</i>, <b>mourn for, for the sake of..,</b> ὡς δὲ πατὴρ οὗ παιδὸς ὀ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 23.222, compare 22.424, 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 4.104, etc.; ὑπέρ τινος 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 387d; ἐπὶ πᾶσι 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “de Virtutibus et Vitiis” 1251b21. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> ὀ. τινί <b>wail</b> or <b>lament to</b> or <b>before,</b> ἐξελθὼν λαιοῖσιν ὀ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 4.740 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ἀλλήλοισιν ὀδύρονται <b>wail aloud</b> one to another, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 2.290. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__4</b></Level3> <i>absolutely</i>, <b>wail, mourn,</b> frequently in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>], in <i>participle</i>, -όμενος στεναχίζω [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 9.13; στοναχῇ τε γόῳ τε ἧσται ὀ. 16.145; ὀ. κατὰ θυμόν 18.203 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; τίταῦτ᾽ ὀδύρομα; why <b>mourn I</b> thus? [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Andromache” 397 (where Pors. restores ταῦτα δύρομαι for the caesura) \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; θρηνοῦντός τε μου καὶ ὀδυρομένου [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Apologia” 38d, compare 1st c.BC: Philodemus Gadarensis Epigrammaticus “Rh.” 1.381 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus, etc. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G8447","accentedUnicode":"ὀδύρομαι","shortDef":"to grieve","mediumDef":"to grieve","stepGloss":"to grieve","stepTransliteration":"oduromai","count":0,"_step_Type":"verb"}]}